==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ricinoleic
<hw>Ric`in*o"le*ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a fatty acid analogous to oleic
acid, obtained from castor oil as an oily substance,
<chform>C18H34O3</chform> with a harsh taste. Formerly written
<altname>ricinolic</altname> and formerly referred to as
<altname>palmic</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ricinoleic acid</ent>⟦br⟧
